Consider a quantum system with two qubits initialized in the state \( |00\rangle \). A sequence of quantum gates is applied to the system as follows:
\[
\begin{align*}
&\text{1. Apply Hadamard gate to qubit 0:} &|00\rangle &\rightarrow \frac{|00\rangle + |10\rangle}{\sqrt{2}} \\
&\text{2. Apply CNOT gate with control on qubit 0 and target on qubit 1:} &\frac{|00\rangle + |10\rangle}{\sqrt{2}} &\rightarrow \frac{|00\rangle + |11\rangle}{\sqrt{2}} \\
&\text{3. Apply RZ gate with angle } \theta \text{ to qubit 1:} &\frac{|00\rangle + |11\rangle}{\sqrt{2}} &\rightarrow \frac{|00\rangle e^{-i\theta/2} + |11\rangle e^{i\theta/2}}{\sqrt{2}}
\end{align*}
\]
Determine the final state of the qubits after these operations and express it in terms of the Pauli-Z operator \( Z \).

